WEBVTT

1
00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:02.780
Where you're starting is not where you have
to stay.

2
00:00:03.400 --> 00:00:08.720
The BMH Group is growing, and the people who
grow with us are the ones who master what's

3
00:00:08.720 --> 00:00:11.880
in front of them and consistently show
they're ready for more.

4
00:00:12.200 --> 00:00:16.680
There's a real path here, and I want you to
see it clearly.

5
00:00:17.960 --> 00:00:23.280
Regardless of the role, you're either working
leads, qualifying sellers, or building

6
00:00:23.280 --> 00:00:25.580
pipelines. That's the foundation.

7
00:00:26.360 --> 00:00:29.600
Everything else at this company builds on
top of that.

8
00:00:30.760 --> 00:00:33.580
Master it. Understand the sellers.

9
00:00:34.100 --> 00:00:35.460
Internalize the pipeline.

10
00:00:35.980 --> 00:00:37.880
Hit your KPIs consistently.

11
00:00:38.460 --> 00:00:43.860
Become the kind of person the team can rely
on, because what you deliver is clean, well

12
00:00:43.860 --> 00:00:46.200
-documented, and actually ready.

13
00:00:47.580 --> 00:00:52.520
Once you've proven you can do that consistently,
hitting your numbers for 90-plus days,

14
00:00:52.960 --> 00:00:57.700
keeping your CRM spotless, showing
leadership qualities, you move up.

15
00:00:58.380 --> 00:01:01.760
At the next level, you're handling more
complex leads.

16
00:01:02.260 --> 00:01:05.180
Probate situations with emotional family
dynamics.

17
00:01:05.660 --> 00:01:09.660
Multi-owner properties, where you've got
three siblings who can't agree on anything.

18
00:01:10.140 --> 00:01:14.520
Sellers who are in financial distress and
need someone who can navigate a sensitive

19
00:01:14.520 --> 00:01:18.980
conversation. You're also mentoring the
newer people coming in behind you.

20
00:01:19.180 --> 00:01:20.920
Earnings can grow with performance.

21
00:01:21.320 --> 00:01:24.600
You've got more autonomy, less daily
oversight.

22
00:01:25.480 --> 00:01:31.780
Beyond that, the next level is where you're
presenting offers, negotiating terms, and

23
00:01:31.780 --> 00:01:33.240
closing deals directly.

24
00:01:33.860 --> 00:01:39.080
You own the full sales cycle from handoff
all the way through to a signed contract.

25
00:01:39.540 --> 00:01:43.840
The earning potential is significantly higher
because you're earning commission on the

26
00:01:43.840 --> 00:01:46.440
deals you close, not just the ones you
source.

27
00:01:47.440 --> 00:01:50.020
But the expectations are higher, too.

28
00:01:50.220 --> 00:01:55.400
You need real negotiation skills, market
knowledge, the ability to structure deals

29
00:01:55.400 --> 00:01:58.840
creatively when the straightforward approach
doesn't work.

30
00:01:59.700 --> 00:02:05.180
And if you have a leadership drive, if you're
the kind of person who gets energy from

31
00:02:05.180 --> 00:02:10.500
building a team and developing other people,
there's a management path where you're

32
00:02:10.500 --> 00:02:15.880
hiring, training, coaching, and owning the
performance of an entire team.

33
00:02:16.440 --> 00:02:20.600
Your compensation at that level is tied to
your team's output.

34
00:02:21.000 --> 00:02:22.900
When they win, you win.

35
00:02:23.900 --> 00:02:27.020
Now, what actually gets you promoted here?

36
00:02:27.500 --> 00:02:30.340
It's not time. Some people advance in six
months.

37
00:02:30.580 --> 00:02:33.420
Some take a year. There's no fixed schedule.

38
00:02:33.580 --> 00:02:37.200
It's entirely based on demonstrated
performance and readiness.

39
00:02:38.200 --> 00:02:40.560
The things we look at are pretty
straightforward.

40
00:02:41.340 --> 00:02:43.040
Are you hitting your numbers consistently?

41
00:02:43.660 --> 00:02:48.640
Not on good days, not when you feel like it,
but every day for extended stretches.

42
00:02:49.180 --> 00:02:51.360
Do your calls actually sound good?

43
00:02:51.780 --> 00:02:57.640
Is your CRM clean? Every lead has notes, a
stage, and a next action.

44
00:02:58.040 --> 00:03:00.320
No leads sitting there with no plan.

45
00:03:01.420 --> 00:03:03.940
We also look at how you contribute to the
team.

46
00:03:04.520 --> 00:03:06.840
Do you help people? Share what's working?

47
00:03:07.420 --> 00:03:09.120
Are you someone others want to work with?

48
00:03:09.420 --> 00:03:10.280
And are you coachable?

49
00:03:10.580 --> 00:03:15.700
When someone points out a gap in your process,
do you fix it or do you get defensive?

50
00:03:16.460 --> 00:03:22.220
The people who advance fastest are the ones
who hear feedback, apply it, and come back

51
00:03:22.220 --> 00:03:24.200
better every time.

52
00:03:24.940 --> 00:03:29.260
And the most obvious one is your work
producing revenue.

53
00:03:29.820 --> 00:03:33.280
Are the people you hand off actually turning
into closed deals?

54
00:03:33.860 --> 00:03:35.960
That speaks louder than anything else.

55
00:03:36.460 --> 00:03:38.260
The BMH Group is expanding.

56
00:03:38.840 --> 00:03:41.900
New markets, new teams, new positions.

57
00:03:42.280 --> 00:03:47.000
The people who are performing well right now
are the first ones considered for every

58
00:03:47.000 --> 00:03:48.560
opportunity that opens up.

59
00:03:48.840 --> 00:03:51.160
How far you go here is up to you.

60
00:03:52.100 --> 00:03:57.740
I hope this gives you a clear picture of the
growth paths available at BMH.

61
00:03:58.300 --> 00:04:02.740
Your path will depend on what you're good
at, where you want to go, and the results you

62
00:04:02.740 --> 00:04:03.140
produce.

63
00:04:03.540 --> 00:04:07.740
We're confident you can continue growing
here if you keep improving and stay open to

64
00:04:07.740 --> 00:04:12.100
coaching. Keep the conversation going about
where you want to grow next.
